        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1961-04-19T20:42:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1961-04-19T20:42:00-05:00" n="156"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d156">
                <head>156. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Joint Chiefs of Staff</gloss> to the
                    Commander in Chief, Atlantic (<persName corresp="#p_DARL1" type="to"
                        >Dennison</persName>)<note n="0" type="source" xml:id="d156fn0">Source:
                        Naval Historical Center, Area Files, Bumpy Road Materials. Top Secret;
                        Operational Immediate; Limited Distribution; Exclusive. Repeated to <gloss
                            target="#t_CTG1">CTG</gloss> 81.8.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1961-04-19T20:42:00-05:00">April 19, 1961, 8:42 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_JCS1">JCS</gloss> 994464. Exclusive for Adm <persName
                        corresp="#p_DARL1">Dennison</persName> and Adm <persName corresp="#p_CRAJE1"
                        >Clark</persName> from <gloss target="#t_JCS1">JCS</gloss>. Bumpy Road.
                    Direct one destroyer to remain off beach during night outside of shore based gun
                    range. Destroyer boat to patrol off beaches to pick up any evacuees. Destroyer
                    keep boat under radar control. Destroyer depart area one hour before sunrise.
                    Report results of search during night and on completion of patrol.<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d156fn1">At 5:10 p.m. <persName corresp="#p_BAAA1">Burke</persName>
                        pressed <persName corresp="#p_CRAJE1">Clark</persName> for more information:
                        “Dammit, make lots of reports. We need data. Even negative helps.” (<gloss
                            target="#t_CNO1">CNO</gloss> telegram 192210Z to <gloss target="#t_CTG1"
                            >CTG</gloss> 81.8, Exclusive for <persName corresp="#p_CRAJE1"
                            >Clark</persName> from <persName corresp="#p_BAAA1">Burke</persName>,
                        April 19; ibid.)</note>
                </p>
                <p>Realize this is most difficult and hazardous assignment but it is necessary.<note
                        n="2" xml:id="d156fn2">The <gloss target="#t_JCS1">JCS</gloss> informed
                            <persName corresp="#p_DARL1">Dennison</persName> at 8:52 that existing
                        instructions with respect to air and surface protection remained in effect,
                        but there was no further requirement for an air <gloss target="#t_CAP1"
                            >CAP</gloss> in the beachhead area. <persName corresp="#p_DARL1"
                            >Dennison</persName> was directed to instruct his naval units in the
                        area, with the exception of <gloss target="#t_CTG1">CTG</gloss> 81.8, to
                        resume normal operations. (<gloss target="#t_JCS1">JCS</gloss> telegram
                        994465 to <gloss target="#t_CINCLANT1">CINCLANT</gloss>, April 19;
                        ibid.)</note>
                </p>
            </div>
